item.title: Latest snapshot of the coronavirus impact
NSW virus death toll hits 48, one new case
item.description: A man aged in his 60s has died in NSW after contracting coronavirus from a personal contact, taking the state's death toll to 48 and nationwide to 99.

item.title: Morrison urges unions, bosses to cooperate
item.description: The prime minister has called for workers and bosses to unite on industrial reforms aimed at stimulating productivity after coronavirus.

item.title: Coronavirus closes 12 Victorian McDonald’s
item.description: Twelve McDonald's outlets have been closed in Victoria due to a coronavirus-infected truck driver, while the state announces $2.7 billion to help revive the economy.

item.title: Vic police upgrade search for missing man
item.description: The search for the remains of a missing Victorian man, who was last seen more than a year ago, will begin in Victoria's southeast.

item.title: News from around the world
item.description: WHO set to host assembly amid controversy

item.title: Air Jordan 1s auctioned for record price
item.description: NBA great Michael Jordan's autographed match-worn sneakers from his rookie season in 1985 have fetched a record $US560,000 ($A873,000) in an online auction.

item.title: Air force show jet crashes in Canada
item.description: A jet from the Canadian air force's Snowbirds exhibition team has crashed into a neighbourhood in the British Columbia city of Kamloops after the pilot ejected, and at least one person was injured, witnesses and officials say.

item.title: Elvis Presley’s Graceland set to reopen
item.description: After shutting down in March due to the coronavirus pandemic, Elvis Presley's Graceland is set to reopen.

item.title: Fisherman falls from trawler off Qld
item.description: Authorities are searching for a fishermen who fell from a trawler in rough weather off Queensland's Sunshine Coast.
